song_name: Hard Rain Coming Down On Me

version_description: Important: This song is in a very non-standard tuning. It is listed as open D, but this is not strictly correct. The song is in DADEAD (not an option in UG's drop down, hence listed as open D). This allows the easy hammer/pull alternation between Dsus2 and D heard in the song during the intro/ when on the D chord for longer periods/ between lines etc. For this reason, the chord diagrams in this tuning are shown at the bottom of the page.
I play this with capo 3 on an acoustic guitar. Think it sounds really good. A great song played in an easy way.
